# InstanceDepth — Integrated Model

Faithful reconstruction of *Instance-Level Video Depth in Groups Beyond
Occlusions* (ICCV 2025), integrated end-to-end.

## Architecture flow
```
RGB → SHARED DINOv2/DPT backbone → [f8,f4,f2]
        ├─ Phase 1 HDI            → init_depth, range_logits      (§4.1)
        ├─ Phase 2 Instance head  → masks, logits, depth_layers   (§4.2.1)
        └─ Phase 3 Refinement     → refined_depth, d_hat          (§4.2.2)
```
The backbone is shared (one ViT-L, not three) — HDI is driven from precomputed
features rather than owning its own encoder.

## Package layout
```
instancedepth/
├── build.py                      # factories incl. build_instance_depth_from_yaml
├── configs/
│   ├── instance_depth.yaml       # unified config (drives all phases)
│   ├── hdi_vitl.yaml             # phase-wise config (legacy/standalone)
│   └── run_config.py             # RunConfig: cross-module consistency
├── models/
│   ├── registry.py               # MODEL_REGISTRY, @register_model
│   ├── instance_depth.py         # integrated InstanceDepth (registered)
│   ├── backbone/dinov2_dpt.py
│   ├── hdi/                       # patch_attention, range_decoder, heads, holistic_depth
│   ├── instance/                  # pixel_decoder, transformer_decoder, query_fusion, instance_head, matcher
│   └── refine/                    # pair_selection, roi_extract, relation_reason, occlusion_refine
├── losses/                        # hdi_losses, instance_losses, refine_losses
└── utils/                         # checkpoint (save/load/load_pretrained), shapes
```

## Quick start
```python
from instancedepth.build import build_instance_depth_from_yaml
model = build_instance_depth_from_yaml("instancedepth/configs/instance_depth.yaml")

out = model(rgb)                       # rgb (B,3,H,W), H,W divisible by 14
out["refined_depth"]                   # (B,1,H,W) final depth
out["init_depth"], out["pred_masks"], out["pred_depth"], out["d_hat"]

# Sec. 4.3 phase schedule
model.set_phase(1)  # train depth range (backbone + hdi)
model.set_phase(2)  # freeze encoder, train instance head
model.set_phase(3)  # freeze instance head, fine-tune encoder+decoder+refine
```

## Configuration system
`RunConfig` owns every sub-config and propagates `max_depth` / `hidden_dim` so
modules cannot drift out of tensor compatibility. Edit `instance_depth.yaml` only.

## Checkpoints
```python
from instancedepth.utils.checkpoint import save_checkpoint, load_checkpoint, load_pretrained
save_checkpoint("m.pth", model, optimizer, step=100, phase=2)
load_checkpoint("m.pth", model)                                   # tolerant resume
load_pretrained(model, da_v2_state, src_prefix="", dst_prefix="backbone.")  # external weights
```

## Verified
Single shared backbone; end-to-end forward; tensor compatibility across all
boundaries; partial-run flags; phase freezing + phase-2 backward; checkpoint
round-trip (bit-identical); prefix-remapped partial weight load. (CPU sandbox
test used ViT-S/reduced sizes; ViT-L is the default config.)

## Confidence labels
Inherited from per-phase READMEs (README_HDI / README_INSTANCE / README_REFINE).
The integration layer itself is [Strongly Inferred] (shared backbone, phase
schedule from §4.3) and [Reasonable Assumption] (registry/config plumbing).
